cred fire. _S_. I, 8, 1 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 3,\n1; P. I, 1, 2; G. I, 5, 16 seq.; 7, 9 seq.; Kh. I, 2, 9 seq.; H. I, 1, 11\nseq.; \xc3\x82p. 1, 12 seq.\n\nf. The purifiers. _S_. I, 8, 14. seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 3, 2 seq.; P. I,\n\np. 300\n\n[paragraph continues] 1, 2; G. I, 7, 21 seq.; Kh. I, 2, 12 seq.; H. I, 1, 23;\n\xc3\x82p. I, 19.\n\ng. Preparation of the \xc3\x82 _g_ ya for sacrifice. _S_. I, 8, 18 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 3, 3;\nP. I, 1, 2 seq.; G. I, 7, 19 seq.; Kh. I, 2, 14 seq.; H. I, 1, 27; \xc3\x82p. I, 22.\n\nh. The \xc3\x82 _g_ ya oblations. _S_. I, 9; \xc3\x82. I, 3, 4 seq.; P. I, 1, 4; 5, 3 seq.;\nG. I, 8; 9, 26 seq.; Kh. I, 3, 12 seq.; H. I, 2, 12 seq.; 3; \xc3\x82p. 2, 5 seq.\n\n7\\. Sacrifices of cooked food. _S_. I, 3; \xc3\x82. I, 10; G. I, 6, 13 seq.; 7 seq.;\nKh. II, 1; \xc3\x82p. 7.\n\n8\\. Animal sacrifice (comp. Ash _t_ aka, Anvash _t_ akya, Sulagava). \xc3\x82. I, 11;\nP. III, 11; G. III, 10, 18-IV, 1; Kh. III, 4; H. II, 15.\n\na. The omentum. \xc3\x82. I, 11, 10 (comp. II, 4, 13); IV, 8, 18; P. III, 11, 4. 6;\nG. III, 10, 30 seq.; IV, 4, 22 seq.; Kh. III, 4, 9 seq. 25 seq.; H. II, 15, 6\nseq.\n\nb. The Avadanas. \xc3\x82. I, II, 12 (comp. II, 4, 54); P. III, 11, 6 seq.; G. IV, 1,\n3. 9 &c.; Kh. III, 4, 14 seq.; H. II, 15, 9 seq.\n\n_________________\n\n9\\. Marriage. _S_. I, 5 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 5 seq.; P. I, 4 seq.; G. II, 1 seq.; Kh.\nI, 3 seq.; H. I, 19 seq.; \xc3\x82p. 2, 12 seq.\n\na. Different kinds of marriage (brahma, daiva, &c.). \xc3\x82. I, 6.\n\nb. Election of the bride. _S_. I, 5, 5 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 5; G. II, 1, 1 seq.; III,\n4, 4 seq.; H. I, 19, 2; \xc3\x82p. 3, 10 seq.\n\nc. The wooers go to the girl's house. _S_. I, 6; \xc3\x82p. 2, 16; 4, 1 seq.\n\nd. Sacrifice when the bride's father has declared his assent. _S_. I, 7 seq.\n\ne. The bride is washed. _S_. I, 11; G. II, 1, 10. 17; Kh. I, 3, 6.\n\nf. Dance of four or eight women. _S_. I, 11, 5.\n\ng. The bridegroom goes to the girl's house. _S_. I, 12.\n\nh. He gives her a garment, anoints her, gives her a mirror, &c. _S_. I, 12, 3\nseq.; P. I, 4, 12 seq.; G. II, 1, 18; Kh. I, 3, 6; \xc3\x82p. 4, 8.\n\ni. Argha at the wedding. _S_. I, 12, 10; G. II, 3, 16 seq.; Kh. I, 4, 7 seq.;\n\xc3\x82p. 3, 5 seq.\n\nk. Sacrifice with the Mahavyah _ri_ tis and other formulas ( _G_ aya,\nAbhyatana, &c., formulas). _S_. I, 12, 11;\n\np. 301\n\n[paragraph continues] \xc3\x82. I, 7, 3; P. I, 5, 3 seq.; G. II, I, 24; Kh. I, 3, 8.\n11; H. I, 19, 7 (comp. 3, 8 seq.; 20, 8); \xc3\x82p. 5, 2. 11 (comp. 2, 7).\n\nl. Seizing of the bride's hand. _S_. I, 13, 2; \xc3\x82. I, 7, 3 seq.; P. I, 7, 3; G.\nII, 2, 16; Kh. I, 3, 17. 31; H. I, 20, 1; \xc3\x82p. 4, 11 seq.\n\nm. The formula, 'This am I, that art thou.' _S_. I, 13, 4; \xc3\x82. I, 7, 6; H. I,\n20, 2.\n\nn. The treading on the stone. _S_. I, 13, 10 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 7, 7; P. I, 7, 1; G.\nII, 2, 3; Kh. I, 3, 19; H. I, 19,8; AP. 5, 3.\n\no. Circumambulation of the fire. _S_. I, 13, 13; \xc3\x82. I, 7, 6; P. I, 5, 1; 7, 3;\nG. II, 2, 8; Kh. I, 3, 24; H. I, 20, 5; \xc3\x82p. 5, 1. 7.\n\np. Sacrifice of fried grain. _S_. I, 13, 15 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 7, 8; P. I, 6, 1 seq.;\nG. II, 2, 5 seq.; Kh. I, 3, 20 seq.; H. I, 20, 3 seq.; \xc3\x82p. 5, 4 seq.\n\nq. The seven steps. _S_. I, 14, 5 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 7, 19; P. I, 8, 1; G. II, 2, 11;\nKh. I, 3, 26; H. I, 20, 9 seq.; 21, 1 seq.; \xc3\x82p. 4, 16.\n\nr. The bride is carried away to her new home. _S_. I, 15; \xc3\x82. I, 7, 21; 8; P.\nI, 8, 10; 10; G. II, 2, 17 seq.; 4; Kh. I, 4, 1 seq.; H. I, 22, 1; \xc3\x82p. 5, 12\nseq.\n\ns. Ceremonies on entering the new home; looking at the polar star. _S_. I, 16,\n17, comp. \xc3\x82. I, 7, 22; comp. P. I, 8, 19; comp. G. II, 3, 5 seq.; 4, 6 seq.;\ncomp. Kh. I, 4, 3; H. I, 22, 6 seq.; \xc3\x82p. 6, 8 seq.\n\nt. The rites of the fourth day; the cohabitation. _S_. I, 18. 19; P. I, 11,\n13; G. II, 5; Kh. I, 4, 12; H. I, 23, 11; 24, 25; \xc3\x82p. 8, 8 seq.\n\n10\\. The Pu _m_ savana (i.e. the ceremony to secure the birth of a male\nch