19\\. The ceremony of shaving the beard (Godana-Karman, Ke _s_ anta). _S_. I,\n28, 18 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 18; P. II, 1, 3 seq.; G. III, 1; Kh. II, 5, 1 seq.; H. II,\n6, 16 seq.; \xc3\x82p. 16, 12 seq.\n\n20\\. The initiation of the student. Studentship. The Samavartana. _S_. II, 1\nseq.; III, 1; IV, 5 seq.; VI; \xc3\x82. I, 19 seq.; III, 5; 8-10; P. II, 2-6; 8;\n10-12; G. II, 10-III, 4; Kh. II, 4-III, I, 32; III, 2, 16-33; H. I, 1 seq.;\nII, 18-20; \xc3\x82p. 10 seq.\n\na. Time of the initiation. The patitasavitrika. _S_. II, 1, 1 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 19,\n1 seq.; P. II, 2, 1 seq.; 5, 36 seq.; G. II, 10, 1 seq.; Kh. II, 4, 1 seq.; H.\nI, 1, 2 seq.; \xc3\x82p. 10, 1 seq.\n\nb. The skin, the girdle, and the staff belonging to the different castes. _S_.\nII. I, 1 seq. 15 seq.; II, 13; \xc3\x82. I, 19, 10 seq.; P. II, 5, 16 seq.; G. II,\n10, 8 seq.; H. I, 1, 17; 4, 7; \xc3\x82p. 11, 16 seq.\n\np. 303\n\nc. Rite of the initiation. _S_. II, 1, 26 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 20, 2 seq.; P. II, 2, 5\nseq.; G. II, 10, 15 seq.; Kh. II, 4, 7 seq.; H. I, 1, 5 seq.; 3, 14 seq.; \xc3\x82p.\n10, 5 seq.\n\nd. The standing duties of the student (begging, putting fuel on the fire,\n&c.). _S_. II, 4, 5; 6; 9; 10; \xc3\x82. I, 20, 11 seq.; 22, 1 seq.; P. II, 2, 2; 4;\n5; G. II, 20, 34. 42 seq.; Kh. II, 4, 19. 25 seq.; H. I, 5, 10; 7, 1 seq. 15\nseq.; 8, 2. 8 seq.; \xc3\x82p. 11, 22 seq.\n\ne. The Savitri. _S_. II, 5 seq.; \xc3\x82. I, 21, 5 seq.; 22, 29; P. II, 3, 3 seq.;\nG. II, 10, 38 seq.; Kh. II, 4, 20 seq.; H. I, 6, 6 seq.; \xc3\x82p. 11, 8 seq.\n\nf. The study of the Veda. _S_. II, 7 seq.; IV, 8; \xc3\x82. I, 22, 12 seq.; III, 5,\n10 seq.; P. III, 16; Kh. III, 2, 22 seq.; H. I, 8, 16.\n\ng. Daily recitation of Vedic texts (svadhyaya). _S_. I, 4; \xc3\x82. III, 2-4.\n\nh. Secret doctrines and special observances connected with them. _S_. II,\n11-12; VI, 1-6; G. III, 1-2; Kh. II, 5.\n\ni. The opening of the annual course of study (Upakara _n_ a). _S_. IV, 5; \xc3\x82.\nIII, 5; P. II, 10; G. II